# Remote Agent Installer for Mac

This script allows you to remotely install an agent on Mac computers within a specified IP range. It provides a user-friendly interface to select a package (pkg) file and automates the installation process on multiple remote machines.

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.x
- `sshpass` command-line utility (for password authentication)
- Mac agent package (pkg) files placed in the 'pkg_folder' directory

## Installation

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:

   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git
Change to the project directory:

sh
Copy code
cd RemoteAgentInstallerforMac
Install the required Python packages (if not already installed):

sh
Copy code
pip install ipaddress
Install sshpass (if not already installed):

sh
Copy code
brew tap linuxbrew/xorg
brew install https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kadwanev/bigboybrew/master/Library/Formula/sshpass.rb
Usage
Place your Mac agent package (pkg) files in the 'pkg_folder' directory.

Open a terminal and navigate to the project directory.

Run the script:

sh
Copy code
python RemoteAgentInstallerforMac.py
Follow the prompts to enter your credentials, IP range, and select the pkg file to install.

